title: 17 Funny Tweets From 2017 So Far That'll Make Canadians Laugh
text:
View this image › 
Twitter: @MrIanMacIntyre ID: 10722136 8. On knowing what winter is REALLY like: My favourite part of La La Land was when the entire theatre laughed at the title screen that said "winter". It's -10 in Canada today.
— Sam Montgomery (@sammontgomery) ID: 10722857 9. On being ridiculous: *Watches Americans deal with Trump* "YOU THOUGHT CANADA WAS A JOKE WELL WHO'S THE JOKE NOW-" *reads headline* "damn… https://t.co/cNWTAgzftz
— Nick Ross (@NickBossRoss) ID: 10722311 10. On acclimating: Aren't you cold in just that t-shirt: the story of being a Canadian abroad
— Alice Moran (@Alice_Moran) ID: 10722316 11. On finding things: Me: do you know where your slippers are dear? Toddler Daughter: ummm...I think they're in Canada? So we've narrowed it down.
— Steve Patterson (@patterballs) ID: 10722366 12. On passive aggression: Sean Spicer: "Yesterday the president had an incredibly productive set of meetings and discussions with PM Joe Trud… https://t.co/jJbNvF9rtA
— Sam Montgomery (@sammontgomery) ID: 10722564 13. On bragging: I'm not saying I'm a big deal but I just got an email from Gap Canada and it wasn't my first one this week.
— Pat Thornton (@patthornton) ID: 10722679 14. On prank shows: Only 3% of Canadian Just for Laughs: Gags bits have resulted in the assassination of a foreign dictator
— Stats Canada (@stats_canada) ID: 10722177 15. On dressing up: What's more formal than a Canadian tuxedo? Debating wearing 3 layers of denim right now
— Rachel West (@rachel_is_here) ID: 10722716 16. On the Ides of March: “Tu Brute, eh?” - Canadian Julius Caesar
— Aaron H.M. (@AaronHM) ID: 10722301 17. And on standing by helplessly: Being Canadian right now is like watching your big brother get his license and then immediately drive the family car into a liquor store.
— Kalvin (@KalvinMacleod) ID: 10722269 Check out more articles on BuzzFeed.com! 
Kat Angus is a staff writer for BuzzFeed and is based in Toronto.
